The paper deals with interference alignment in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed method involves antenna switching, which is a technique used in signal processing (cs.SI) and the paper also discusses the use of supersymbols, which is a concept related to multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents theoretical results and performance analysis, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG).
